        <section xml:id="CHANGE_ME3">
            <info>
                <title xml:id="CHANGE_ME3.title">Create conversations</title>
            </info>
            <para>Communication in &chat_client; takes place in the context of conversations. A
                conversation may contain just two particpants, or it may include a large group. The
                first thing that a new user of &chat_client; must do is create a conversation. Each
                participating contact also creates a conversation.</para>
            <para><emphasis role="bold">To create a conversation</emphasis></para>
            <para>
                <procedure>
                    <step>
                        <para>Open &chat_client;.</para>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <para>In the toolbar, click the <guilabel>New conversation</guilabel>
                            button.</para>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <para>In the <guilabel>New conversation</guilabel> window, type a name in
                            the <guilabel>Choose conversation name</guilabel> field. This name is
                            how you identify the conversation in your own &chat_client; client. It
                            may differ from what your contacts call their corresponding
                            conversations. Click <guilabel>OK</guilabel> when finished.</para>
                    </step>
                    <step>
                        <para>Type a name for yourself in the field labeled <guilabel>Choose (your)
                                name displayed to the other user(s)</guilabel>. Click
                                <guilabel>OK</guilabel> when finished. Your contacts will see this
                            name when the accept your invitation,
                            <?oxy_comment_start author="dwrob" timestamp="20251105T173215-0800" comment="Is this actually supported?"?>although
                            they may assign some other name to you<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
                    </step>
                </procedure>               
            </para>
            <para>In the left pane of the client, labeled <guilabel>Conversations and
                    contacts</guilabel>, the name of your new conversation is displayed along with
                your own name as the first contact. In the right pane, labeled
                    <guilabel>Messages</guilabel>,
                &chat_client;<?oxy_comment_start author="dwrob" timestamp="20251105T173304-0800" comment="This should look more like a stage direction than like a regular message."?>
                prints a greeting message<?oxy_comment_end?>.</para>
            <para>You can create
                <?oxy_comment_start author="dwrob" timestamp="20251105T173506-0800" comment="Is there in fact a limitation, other than all available RAM?"?>any
                number<?oxy_comment_end?> of conversations, each completely separate from the
                others.</para>
        </section>
